  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b89\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Factors that browse freely",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "MP Patali Champika Ranawaka said that key figures in the fuel crisis were continuing to hold high positions in the government and accused those responsible for the fuel crisis of moving freely.",
        "He said this while commenting to the media in Colombo today (27).",
        "He accused the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation of registering companies to procure fuel, although the government was trying to procure fuel through unsolicited proposals.",
        "He said that despite promising to import six fuel exports, not a single ship had arrived in Sri Lanka recently.",
        "He noted that vehicles were severely affected due to the quality of fuel when substandard fuel was imported in 2012.",
        "He said timely bids and immediate bids were in place and unsolicited proposals would affect fuel supply and cause severe damage."
      ],
